            "heading": "Main space",
            "paragraphs": [
                "The two large railway arches off Whiston road have been decorated by Turning Earth with a beautiful interior that showcases the arches themselves and compliments their previous use as an industrial glassworks, but which also creates an environment with which to showcase British craft and the 'handmade modern' aesthetic movement that is beginning to sweep our country. Turning Earth put in large glass frontages and a traditional wooden timber framed mezzanine, made in greenwood by a British designer-maker."
